{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '1. **2026-03-30 | LG Innotek & Applied Intuition Strategic Partnership**\n   LG Innotek officially partnered with US-based Silicon Valley software developer Applied Intuition to accelerate its entry into the physical AI market. The joint venture aims to expand autonomous driving camera sensing modules into broader applications, including drones, heavy equipment, and embodied robotics, leveraging virtual sensors and simulation. \n   *Source URL: https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/tech/2026/03/129_394982.html*\n\n2. **2026-03-30 | NHTSA Probe Threatens Tesla\'s "Physical AI" Valuation**\n   The U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) intensified its Engineering Analysis (EA26002) into Tesla\'s camera-only autonomous driving tech. The regulatory probe explicitly threatens Tesla\'s "camera-only vision," posing a severe hardware redesign risk and creating systemic headwinds for Tesla\'s $1.1T valuation tied to its physical AI thesis (Optimus humanoids and Cybercabs).\n   *Source URL: https://www.forbes.com/sites/bradtempleton/2026/03/30/tesla-valuation-threatened-by-nhtsa-probe-of-full-self-driving/*\n\n3. **2026-03-29 | Hesai Group Pivots Strategy to Emphasize Physical AI**\n   During its fiscal 2025 earnings briefing, Hesai Group (NASDAQ: HSAI) management announced a strategic transition beyond traditional autonomous driving, signaling a deep pivot into Physical AI and robotics. The company teased the upcoming launch of two "groundbreaking" vision and sensing products specifically designed for embodied AI and next-generation robotics platforms over the coming months.\n   *Source URL: https://www.investing.com/news/stock-market-news/hesai-management-pivots-to-physical-ai-plans-two-new-products-93CH-3942353*'}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 465, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT',