{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '### Physical AI and Embodied Robotics: Daily Data Engineering Report\n\n#### 1. LG Innotek & Applied Intuition Strategic Partnership\n*   **Direct Impact:** LG Innotek has established a joint venture with Applied Intuition to integrate its camera sensing modules with virtual sensors and simulation software. \n*   **Market Dynamics:** Represents a critical crossover of autonomous vehicle sensing IP into the broader physical AI ecosystem (drones, heavy equipment, embodied robotics).\n*   **Sentiment:** **Bullish**\n\n#### 2. NHTSA Probe Threatens Tesla\'s "Physical AI" Valuation\n*   **Direct Impact:** NHTSA\'s Engineering Analysis (EA26002) specifically targets Tesla\'s "camera-only vision" tech, introducing severe hardware redesign and regulatory compliance risks.\n*   **Indirect Impact:** A potential forced pivot away from pure-vision could cascade into systemic headwinds for Tesla’s physical AI ecosystem, jeopardizing the foundational thesis behind its Optimus humanoid and Cybercab product lines.\n*   **Sentiment:** **Bearish**\n*   **Ticker Data (TSLA):** Trading lower around $361.80, facing notable YTD technical headwinds as regulatory pressures test elevated multiples.\n\n#### 3. Hesai Group (HSAI) Pivots Strategy to Emphasize Physical AI\n*   **Direct Impact:** Hesai\'s FY25 earnings call revealed a strategic pivot toward physical AI, announcing two new vision and sensing products specifically built for embodied robotics.\n*   **Market Dynamics:** Validates an accelerating trend of LiDAR and sensor companies diversifying away from purely automotive ADAS dependencies to capture adjacent robotics total addressable markets (TAMs).\n*   **Sentiment:** **Bullish**\n*   **Ticker Data (HSAI):** Trading near $18.50, seeking momentum following broader EV market slowdowns.'}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 391, '