{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': 'Here are the critical, high-signal developments in Space Exploration and Defense Technology from the last 24-48 hours:\n\n1. **Advent International $1B Defense Tech Commitment & Shield AI Series G**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-29\n   - **Context**: Global private equity firm Advent International announced a $1 billion commitment to next-generation defense technology. As part of this, Advent has signed a definitive agreement to co-lead a $1.5 billion Series G funding round for autonomous systems developer Shield AI, valuing the company at $12.7 billion.\n   - **Source**: https://pulse2.com/advent-1-billion-commitment-to-next-generation-defense-technology-investment-strategy (Pulse 2.0)\n\n2. **SpaceX Prepares for Unprecedented Mega-IPO**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Context**: Market rumors and reports indicate SpaceX is laying the groundwork for what could be the largest Initial Public Offering (IPO) in history. Expectations suggest the listing could raise more capital than all U.S. listings combined in 2024 and 2025.\n   - **Source**: https://www.axios.com/ (Axios) \n\n3. **Northrop Grumman Tests New Sentinel ICBM Silo Prototype**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-29\n   - **Context**: Northrop Grumman and the U.S. Air Force began testing a newly designed, modular prototype launch tube for the Sentinel intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM) program. Developed with Bechtel, the prototype aims to streamline construction, reduce costs, and accelerate the deployment of the U.S.\'s modernized land-based nuclear deterrent.\n   - **Source**: https://seekingalpha.com/news/northrop-u-s-air-force-test-new-missile-silo-design-for-sentinel-program (Seeking Alpha)\n\n4. **SpaceX Transporter-16 Rideshare Mission**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-29\n   - **Context**: SpaceX scheduled the launch of 119 payloads to orbit via a Falcon 9 rocket from Vandenberg Space Force Base. The payloads include advanced optical inter-satellite link payloads from Spire Global and AAC Clyde Space, backed by UK Space Agency funding, designed to drastically reduce data latency for aerospace and defense applications.\n   - **Source**: https://www.space.com/watch-spacex-launch-119-payloads-california-march-30 (Space.com) / https://www.gov.uk/government/news/scottish-space-companies-pioneer-next-generation-satellite-communications-with-spacex-launch (GOV.UK)\n\n5. **NASA Declares Artemis II "Go" for Approaching Launch Window**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Context**: NASA completed its final preparations and officially declared readiness for the historic Artemis II crewed flight around the moon. The immediate launch window opens on April 1, 2026.\n   - **Source**: https://www.livescience.com/we-are-getting-very-very-close-nasa-makes-final-artemis-ii-preparations (Live Science)', 'thought_signature': 'CpcCAY89a19cPUe9k8p175VkxNSVinA0U2bNUhvRGB8Y8z2Zi-uewwJbt1BdOy9GB1w7YSvYjjAlM7du7WKCOO62eUvYdr0F75cqh4trfGtzMJovd_EThC2vV9y-kvK0nRlNDhCaCYOaDiHh6jZUe7IISvAnCpDCkjJBhu0iJ8dDbMxnybUnpie4bpen9JlRYaKizf_Z-11lE3FSBpY7uj7X_d-kEfpomJqs7hHXuGY6GpSCzCjJUxZsvw5W3S_--0CBdkI0TBb2Hgk8axNWQmFEwDKh-NTGGuqqniBBEFveXIJ9i3y0cKhIh5b0AMgE4wx78K0xudmPO2-P1FJg90rgzdu0k1zpDxVZP8YtYHlyESv6TewU34ubCoYWAY89a1_HuhxVlawGgy7FZm5rSH4oIezMrr3ClEZKDBx7YxwZsmX8r5Y7vkoGB_SCjhpgmQteKRP70mcTcjjP44QRjJ92t6sKNHGxBdGWt-v9fg1FskbYas2-7obcO7kRc5N-Ut2s6BtzdyA34rsDFYMVrw-2Sq2BiIUL81mqhnni4fEZwmHIMreaxHtbx6HTQCntgJHoDDwHnY2r3KZAkpkW_AXu87372R5mKSEo0WFtGvSTGfm6cO8MhuA7YEg4gQ0WqvgNqCEmHFtd0oSP5sNQQPfCXTBD-S1HLpc3LYNZ5V74v92FH7VdJz_EowqQuGdzlJ4kPmHh85-m8YS1Tt3QIQNU9BRzt8xieBiX2tMXG1iHSjL1edl6gO-L2Tf9Fa3_fmgpySDLLEyRtTm109HDWM_DSBjGD1dcR9dwJVgvNBz9JEy4s09DzztFmuxTH9vzXnH1op5IwTcAZmPtYghG3xCj48illi7CTIicOTmPJLxVZIIO6v9L_wGRcF28W0-It8XGxp4SuW-iXVzkVa2xRQP0oAtuEA7bD1SnEkePoYxixUklTZjGkctlw0ggmoWUEb3IF4jo5MMS4P3h3xnxVCNkmW5v6b3SOx2VEhL8CUkW7Mcc8nMIr_IsJr8MHq2dhebfe2X-ERRhwVSyCvH46X9g6fGTefc3orK8rdBmeK17ZJkFsVuV86MWicc8nhJDEuNcS2q-Hmi3PV-fGBwoKtHsquoMG