Silo Prototype**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-29\n   - **Context**: Northrop Grumman and the U.S. Air Force began testing a newly designed, modular prototype launch tube for the Sentinel intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM) program. Developed with Bechtel, the prototype aims to streamline construction, reduce costs, and accelerate the deployment of the U.S.\'s modernized land-based nuclear deterrent.\n   - **Source**: https://seekingalpha.com/news/northrop-u-s-air-force-test-new-missile-silo-design-for-sentinel-program (Seeking Alpha)\n\n4. **SpaceX Transporter-16 Rideshare Mission**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-29\n   - **Context**: SpaceX scheduled the launch of 119 payloads to orbit via a Falcon 9 rocket from Vandenberg Space Force Base. The payloads include advanced optical inter-satellite link payloads from Spire Global and AAC Clyde Space, backed by UK Space Agency funding, designed to drastically reduce data latency for aerospace and defense applications.\n   - **Source**: https://www.space.com/watch-spacex-launch-119-payloads-california-march-30 (Space.com) / https://www.gov.uk/government/news/scottish-space-companies-pioneer-next-generation-satellite-communications-with-spacex-launch (GOV.UK)\n\n5. **NASA Declares Artemis II "Go" for Approaching Launch Window**\n   - **Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Context**: NASA completed its final preparations and officially declared readiness for the historic Artemis II crewed flight around the moon. The immediate launch window opens on April 1, 2026.\n   - **Source**: https://www.livescience.com/we-are-getting-very-very-close-nasa-makes-final-artemis-ii-preparations (Live Science)'}, 'artifact_delta': {}, 'requested_auth_configs': {}, 'requested_tool_confirmations': {}}, 'branch': 'Batch_2.Space_Defense_Scout_Pipeline', 'id': '73bc3ced-e313-4a33-baa4-fc8a94271a65', 'timestamp': 1774904525.7139246}Tools at indices [0] are not compatible with automatic function calling (AFC). AFC is disabled. If AFC is intended, please include p