{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '**AI Stack Market Sweep Findings**\n\n**1. Accesso acquires Dexibit for AI Analytics Platform Launch**\n* **Date:** 2026-03-30\n* **Details:** Ticketing and technology provider Accesso acquired Dexibit to power its new AI analytics platform targeted at the visitor attractions industry. \n* **Source:** [Attractions Management](https://www.attractionsmanagement.com/index.cfm?pagetype=news&codeID=353457)\n* **Analysis:**\n   * **Direct:** Accesso expands its AI analytics capabilities for visitor attractions and the entertainment industry.\n   * **Indirect:** Dexibit\'s platform gains deeper integration into traditional ticketing pipelines, enabling data-driven operational up-sells.\n   * **Market Dynamics:** Traditional software and service providers are actively acquiring AI point-solutions to remain competitive against fully modern tech stacks. \n   * **Sentiment:** Bullish\n* **Ticker Data:** Accesso Technology Group plc (LON: ACSO). Currently trading around 250 - 252 GBp with a market cap of approximately £80M. \n\n**2. OpenAI Acquires Developer Tools Astral & Promptfoo**\n* **Date:** 2026-03-25\n* **Details:** Accelerating its developer ecosystem M&A, OpenAI acquired Astral (creators of open-source Python tools like Ruff) and Promptfoo (an open-source framework for testing and evaluating LLM apps).\n* **Source:** [San Francisco Business Times](https://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/news/2026/03/25/openai-acquires-startups-astral-promptfoo.html)\n* **Analysis:**\n   * **Direct:** OpenAI significantly bolsters its native developer tooling footprint with open-source Python and LLM testing frameworks.\n   * **Indirect:** Open-source maintainers are finding highly lucrative exits with foundational AI labs, effectively tightening OpenAI\'s grip on the developer lifecycle.\n   * **Market Dynamics:** Rapid consolidation of the AI developer stack. Foundation model providers want end-to-end control of app creation, testing, and deployment.\n   * **Sentiment:** Bullish\n* **Ticker Data:** Private\n\n**3. Shield AI Secures $1.5B Series G & Acquires Aechelon Technology**\n* **Date:** 2026-03-26\n* **Details:** AI defense tech "whale" Shield AI announced a $1.5 billion Series G funding round—propelling its valuation to $12.7 billion—and simultaneously acquired Aechelon Technology to enhance its AI aviation simulations.\n* **Source:** [San Diego Union-Tribune](https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/2026/03/26/shield-ai-raises-massive-series-g-acquires-aechelon/)\n* **Analysis:**\n   * **Direct:** Shield AI secures an immense $12.7B valuation and strategically adds aviation simulation capabilities to its defense portfolio.\n   * **Indirect:** Defense-sector AI applications are experiencing unprecedented, continuous capital inflows, enabling rapid M&A. \n   * **Market Dynamics:** The AI defense race is minting private "whales" that are exceptionally capitalized and actively acquiring specialized hardware and simulation tech to dominate government contracts. \n   * **Sentiment:** Very Bullish\n* **Ticker Data:** Private', 'thought_signature': 'CmoBjz1rXyZJse2DOBv1UkP9xR3WpPKCvu1I3rWlyM5IIZ-a30k1kgUiB7_nAzCSqaHm3Wqt9xOzr_0WdOd6jO6CdR1P5MXNycjfuMubMIAEJmklqc2G-Is6460OV-UqX4yTnh-lazbOmzq9CooWAY89a1_zGazpmCqIGN7a501-OUGbfkpNUyFfiGCo9qOPOXx0tDH9hmt9giRK17u1idt03BHLLNHRvMEY9BbPL-pjcjjOW80SHMk8PWTQBEtiUkksvgbTkWqOTwh992orfAO1vAH_SExHzErBDPr70JWrLAyQlonUewr1l93vPtI5w5M2dWxxIroeIzs91_1sTvHvH2LYd-mV98LAH1dEmzdvqfHdKdDM3G7Nx5j11Er-gOuvnwCyRcVNVugwQr0dlRCCx5qqMI1keceETe3FHDoiarIHWT2Gp2bHeGamJzgAI9AWAlxylGJFuCIoxAPChuFHt30XBVyHqyVpaT3NEkvgiyTuVI_J2lHkTnFeGNoUmUeAZHOhWd2ks73M0n7qlRmEnG0cv024pKFF3VG8eYCAhLv6HgCR9PRVtmnqvk4lsXefM0WKFopQhY6XFoOJw0h3H_PaKJk8QMK4IH8TmN0u6_JOuUESl-Vk2nOj6EJVXs5T97pXCxBqPdumHDRc3hV4WgtiE23Nv3QmMBpl_9x_IVyYm0jKkQCic1y4EoTiaUgMX4zK6eb5ys5xl9bMxxMaBlsq7pjvP___usrQdntGEQOrKYs1L3OHMZe0QLVdGIkUopeX9hrH-KsYSH-ljr7jTHpjSlWp8Z8z6eD1ZCK0PshPTaXZQsajld716w9GNGaONydO