m JADC2 proxy. |\n| **2026-03-30** | **NASA Declares Artemis II "Go"**<br>NASA completed final preparations and declared readiness for the historic Artemis II crewed flight, with the launch window opening April 1, 2026. | **Bullish**<br>First crewed moon mission in over 50 years is officially cleared for launch. Validates the immense sunk capital in the SLS architecture and Orion capsule, generating massive political goodwill and safeguarding near-term lunar exploration budgets. | **Volatility Play**<br>Legacy prime contractors (LMT for Orion, BA for SLS core) get a temporary sentiment boost, but lunar infrastructure players stand to gain the most speculative momentum. Watch LUNR for explosive volatility spikes. | **Tickers**: LUNR, RKLB, LMT, BA.<br>**Levels**: Watch for speculative call buying and elevated IV in LUNR leading strictly into the April 1 launch week. |\n\n*End of Sweep.*', 'thought_signature': 'ClABjz1rXwS_uym6-jABr7LB73ETcfLwwLigt3zEjgr-kaayIYR3_6jn7mKMtnOeHJgGRwIFe0Grra7Gn8Y26AAhzDxJawvY1QpUC_WyJNGy_w=='}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 1246, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 1246}], 'prompt_token_count': 5257, 'prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 5257}], 'thoughts_token_count': 9, 'total_token_count': 6512, 'traffic_type': 'ON_DEMAND'}, 'invocation_id': 'e-aa88a0b0-a1f3-4b00-89d2-ba0426d5faeb', 'author': 'Space_Defense_Scout_Strategist', 'actions': {'state_delta': {'Space_Defense_Scout_report': '### Daily Market Sweep: Space Exploration and Defense Technology\n\nHere are the deduplicated, high-signal findings from the last 24-48 hours, enriched with layered analysis and current market data.\n\n| Datetime | Finding | Sentiment & Investment Takeaways | Guidance & Play | Market Data & Levels |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **2026-03-29** | **Advent Int. $1B Defense Tech Fund & Shield AI Series G**<br>A