se takeover of Good2Go4 Corp., accompanied by an $8 million brokered private placement. Capital will be aggressively deployed to advance the 100% owned SBH Project in Alberta, recognized as one of the largest North American accumulations of critical minerals and REEs housed within black shale deposits.\n*Source: [InvestorNews](https://investornews.com)*\n\n4. **Cobalt Blue & Glomar Minerals Launch "Project Infinity" Consortium** (2026-03-29) \nCobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals have partnered to launch a deep-sea minerals consortium targeted at constructing a U.S.-based polymetallic nodule processing facility. Scaled for an initial annual throughput of 200,000 tonnes, the facility pairs Glomar\'s marine extraction licenses with Cobalt Blue\'s proprietary metallurgy tech to extract critical metals including cobalt, nickel, manganese, copper, and REEs.\n*Source: [Shanghai Metals Market / SMM](https://news.metal.com)*'}, 'artifact_delta': {}, 'requested_auth_configs': {}, 'requested_tool_confirmations': {}}, 'branch': 'Batch_3.Strategic_Minerals_Scout_Pipeline', 'id': '4407ae23-a6e3-4f0a-8419-90b359a2bcb2', 'timestamp': 1774904899.2965157}
