{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'function_call': {'id': 'adk-5acdd460-14e9-489f-a106-0321acfb39d6', 'args': {'category': 'Strategic Minerals', 'scout_findings_json': '["USA Rare Earth (USAR) released a financial update confirming it expects to finalize definitive documentation for a $1.6 billion U.S. Department of Commerce funding package under the CHIPS Program in April 2026. The company also announced the March 2026 commissioning of Phase 1A of its Stillwater, Oklahoma magnet manufacturing line (aiming for 600 MTPA by Q4 2026). First commercial production from its flagship Round Top heavy rare earth project in Texas has been officially pushed back to late 2028. Note: The funding package is drawing political scrutiny from House Democrats over potential conflicts involving Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick.", "EnergyX successfully launched the first direct lithium extraction (DLE) plant in Texas. The facility launch represents a massive catalyst for domestic U.S. lithium independence, bypassing traditional, slower evaporation pond techniques to serve the North American EV and battery storage supply chain.", "Critical Minerals Americas Inc. (CMAI) executed a reverse takeover of Good2Go4 Corp., accompanied by an $8 million brokered private placement. Capital will be aggressively deployed to advance the 100% owned SBH Project in Alberta, recognized as one of the largest North American accumulations of critical minerals and REEs housed within black shale deposits.", "Cobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals have partnered to launch a deep-sea minerals consortium targeted at constructing a U.S.-based polymetallic nodule processing facility. Scaled for an initial annual throughput of 200,000 tonnes, the facility pairs Glomar\'s marine extraction licenses with Cobalt Blue\'s proprietary metallurgy tech to extract critical metals including cobalt, nickel, manganese, copper, and REEs."]'}, 'name': 'dedup_findings'}, 'thought_signature': 'CkgBjz1rXz9