{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '### Power Generation and Energy Storage Market Sweep: Processed Findings\n\n#### 1. ArtIn Energy Secures $255M Investment\n- **Direct:** ArtIn Energy received $255M from Agila Investments, bringing its valuation to $14.58B to scale its utility-scale solar and BESS platform.\n- **Indirect:** Demonstrates massive appetite for integrated solar/storage platforms with mature execution capabilities, rewarding them with decacorn-level valuations.\n- **Market Dynamics:** Private capital continues to funnel aggressively into top-tier renewable infrastructure holding companies.\n- **Sentiment:** Very Bullish\n\n#### 2. esVolta Finalizes $139.6M Texas BESS Financing\n- **Direct:** esVolta secured $139.6M in project financing for its 150-MW / 300-MWh Boxcar Energy Storage project in Wylie, Texas.\n- **Indirect:** Texas (ERCOT) remains a highly attractive merchant market for 2-hour battery storage deployments.\n- **Market Dynamics:** Debt markets are highly comfortable underwriting large-scale merchant or semi-merchant storage assets in volatile grid regions.\n- **Sentiment:** Bullish\n\n#### 3. Arevon Breaks Ground on $600M California Asset\n- **Direct:** Arevon commenced construction on the $600M, 250 MW / 1 GWh Cormorant BESS in Daly City, California.\n- **Indirect:** 4-hour duration batteries are cementing their status as critical grid infrastructure in CAISO to support evening peak loads and displace peaker plants.\n- **Market Dynamics:** Megaprojects requiring over half a billion in capex are successfully moving past development hurdles and into construction.\n- **Sentiment:** Very Bullish\n\n#### 4. Crédit Agricole Assurances (CAA) Acquires Stake in Whysol\n- **Direct:** CAA took a minority stake in Italian developer Whysol Renewables to access its 864 MW BESS pipeline.\n- **Indirect:** Institutional insurance capital is eager to acquire early or mid-stage European storage pipelines to meet long-term ESG and yield targets.\n- **Market Dynamics:** M&A activity is shifting upstream towards developers with strong interconnection queues in emerging BESS markets like Italy.\n- **Sentiment:** Bullish\n\n#### 5. Akuo Secures EU Grant for Portugal Co-located Storage\n- **Direct:** Akuo Energy secured a €15M EU Innovation Fund grant for its 80 MW / 220 MWh "SantasBAT" BESS, co-located with a 181 MW solar farm.\n- **Indirect:** Co-location is gaining momentum in Iberia, supported by robust public incentive structures to alleviate solar curtailment.\n- **Market Dynamics:** European subsidies remain a vital catalyst for accelerating utility-scale storage deployments alongside existing renewable capacity.\n- **Sentiment:** Bullish\n\n#### 6. XPLR Infrastructure Executes NextEra (NEE) Options\n- **Direct:** XPLR OpCo acquired a 49% equity interest in four NextEra Energy Resources battery storage joint ventures. \n- **Indirect:** NextEra continues its strategy of capital recycling, bringing in infrastructure partners to monetize operational or late-stage assets and fund future development.\n- **Market Dynamics:** Joint ventures and minority stake sales are critical vehicles for major utilities to manage balance sheets while dominating the storage pipeline. \n- **Sentiment:** Bullish', 'thought_signature': 'CkMBjz1rXyQhqgBMtmvNDDqC6D7jODv4sfi1XU7Jb9ZxEfzjQMqpkthKvAzuxMpt3FMvFaXc9G0n9LQzn0a57A-7efQi'}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 733, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 733}], 'prompt_token_count': 2937, 'prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 2937}], 'thoughts_token_count': 8, 'total_token_count': 3678, 'traffic_type': 'ON_DEMAND'}, 'invocation_id': 'e-a1a42493-ad48-4a5d-9e01-5c4812ffacba', 'author': 'Power_Energy_Scout_DE', 'actions': {'state_delta': {'Power_Energy_Scout_analyzed': '### Power Generation and Energy Storage Market Sweep: 