 Wait for the stock to resume trading post-RTO under the new ticker CMAI on the TSXV, and establish a clear technical base before taking an initial position.', 'finding': 'Critical Minerals Americas Inc. (CMAI) completed a reverse takeover of Good2Go4 Corp. and raised $8 million to advance its SBH black shale project in Alberta.', 'findings_date': '2026-03-30'}, 'name': 'append_to_memory_log'}}, {'function_call': {'id': 'adk-36ab78be-cb50-4e77-a4d9-bbb1ec0e2817', 'args': {'finding': 'Cobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals have launched a deep-sea minerals consortium targeted at constructing a U.S.-based 200,000 MTPA polymetallic nodule processing facility.', 'category': 'Strategic Minerals', 'guidance_play': 'Position in COB.AX for medium-term upside as DSM processing scales. The stock has broken out technically with strong recent momentum. Buy near current levels with a stop loss around $0.072.', 'findings_date': '2026-03-29', 'insights_sentiment': 'Bullish. Accelerates the commercial viability of deep-sea mining (DSM) by resolving onshore processing bottlenecks. Establishing U.S. processing infrastructure for seafloor nodules could reshape the nickel, cobalt, and manganese supply curves over the next decade.', 'price_levels': 'ASX:COB trading at AUD $0.084. Strong upside potential with analyst consensus price target of AUD $0.20. Support at $0.072, near-term resistance at $0.086.'}, 'name': 'append_to_memory_log'}}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {'retrieval_metadata': {}, 'search_entry_point': {'rendered_content': '<style>\n.container {\n  align-items: center;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  display: flex;\n  font-family: Google Sans, Roboto, sans-serif;\n  font-size: 14px;\n  line-height: 20px;\n  padding: 8px 12px;\n}\n.chip {\n  display: inline-block;\n  border: solid 1px;\n  border-radius: 16px;\n  min-width: 14px;\n  padding: 5px 16px;\n  text-align: center;\n  user-select: none;\n  margin: 0 8px;\n  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\n}\n.carousel {\n  