unding to date. |\n| **2026-03-30** | **Critical Minerals Americas Inc. (CMAI) Executes Reverse Takeover & Capital Raise**<br>CMAI completed a reverse takeover of Good2Go4 Corp. and raised $8 million to advance its SBH black shale project in Alberta. | **Bullish**<br>Showcases sustained investor appetite for large-scale, unconventional critical mineral deposits in safe jurisdictions like Canada. Black shale REE deposits are gaining traction as a viable alternative to traditional hard-rock and ionic clay mining. | **Wait and See**<br>Speculative positioning. Wait for the stock to resume trading post-RTO under the new ticker CMAI on the TSXV, and establish a clear technical base before taking an initial position. | **TSXV: GFOR.P (transitioning to CMAI)**<br>Trading halted pending RTO completion.<br>Backed by new $8M brokered private placement. |\n| **2026-03-29** | **Cobalt Blue & Glomar Minerals Launch "Project Infinity" Consortium**<br>The consortium plans to build a 200,000 MTPA polymetallic nodule processing facility in the U.S. using Glomar\'s marine extraction and Cobalt Blue\'s metallurgy. | **Bullish**<br>Accelerates the commercial viability of deep-sea mining (DSM) by resolving onshore processing bottlenecks. Establishing U.S. processing infrastructure for seafloor nodules could reshape the nickel, cobalt, and manganese supply curves over the next decade. | **Position for Breakout**<br>Position in COB.AX for medium-term upside as DSM processing scales. The stock has broken out technically with strong recent momentum. Buy near current levels with a stop loss around $0.072. | **ASX: COB**<br>Trading at AUD $0.084.<br>Strong upside potential with analyst consensus price target of AUD $0.20.<br>Support at $0.072, near-term resistance at $0.086. |', 'thought_signature': 'CisBjz1rX_QFCqVho1xbBOezJ7JujeGon-GnyP6DuaFJvB24cV6qVW_DASdc'}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 947, 'candidates